BusinessTech will host the 2019 FinTech Conference on 11 September 2019 at The Venue in Melrose Arch. The conference will focus on all aspects of financial technology and is a must-attend event for professionals and executives working in the South African financial, technology and telecoms sectors. The Emcee for the event is The Money Show’s Bruce Whitfield, who will be joined by fintech experts from South Africa’s top financial and technology companies. Topics which will be covered include digital and mobile banking, fintech disruption, mobile payments, digital banking, cryptocurrency, blockchain, cyber security, AI and machine learning. BusinessTech editor Gareth Vorster said the financial services industry in South Africa is awash with new innovation, led by startups and supported by traditional firms who have increased their budgets to invest in new technology. The FinTech Conference, Vorster said, will provide delegates with better insight into this rapidly growing industry. Register now Registrations for the 2019 FinTech Conference opened this week with early-bird tickets offering a big discount to delegates. For more information and to register, visit: 2019 FinTech Conference Website